In [[algebra]], the '''distribution algebra''' <math>D(G, K)</math> of a [[p-adic Lie group|''p''-adic Lie group]] ''G'' is the ''K''-algebra of ''K''-valued distributions on ''G''. (See the reference for a more precise definition.)

