In geometry, '''sphere packing in a cube''' is a three-dimensional [[sphere packing]] problem with the objective of packing [[sphere]]s inside a [[cube]]. It is the three-dimensional equivalent of the [[circle packing in a square]] problem in two dimensions. The problem consists of determining the optimal packing of a given number of spheres inside the cube.

